Prequesits
===========

Firs of all, install the Java interface for 
warc-tools (see contrib/java/install)



Settings
=========

See section "2.3 Installation" for JHOVE installation process:
http://hul.harvard.edu/jhove/using.html

$ cd contrib/jhove
$ wget http://hul.harvard.edu/jhove/jhove-1_1.tar.gz
$ tar xf jhove-1_1.tar.gz
$ export JHOVE_HOME=`pwd`/jhove

The following variables in $JHOVE_HOME/conf/jhove.conf need to be set:

<jhoveHome>jhove-home-directory</jhoveHome>
<tempDirectory>temporary-directory</tempDirectory>

Also, change the following variables in the file "jhove.tmpl" like this:

#JHOVE_HOME=[your directory path]/jhove
#JAVA_HOME=/usr/java
JAVA=$JAVA_HOME/bin/java



Building
=========

$ cd warc-tools-read-only
$ make java
$ cd contrib/jhove
$ tar xf patch.tar.gz -C $JHOVE_HOME
$ cd $JHOVE_HOME
$ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=../../..:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH

or on Mac OS X:
$ export DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=../../..:$DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH

Then:
$ ant




Testing
========

Validate the warc file "../awanvl.warc" in "contrib/java" with JHOVE:
$ ./jhove.tmpl -c conf/jhove.conf ../../java/awanvl.warc 

